## Problem
Non-Grok `XMLHttpRequest` paths have no `timeout` and no generation/token to ignore stale responses after rediscover or profile list replacement. A slow XHR from a previous refresh can call `applyUsageResult(idx, …)` against a different profile that now occupies that index after `mergeDiscovered` rebuilds `profiles`.

## Location
contents/ui/ProfileController.qml:532-561

## Suggested fix
Store `profile.id` + fetch generation on each request; ignore callbacks when gen/id mismatch; set `xhr.timeout` like Grok (25s) and clear `loading` on timeout.

## Source
Review ff0a2eec Issue 8

## Partial fix note (2026-07-15, response-cache merge)
`fetchUsage` now sets `xhr.timeout = 25000` and uses a settle-once path (shared with timeout). **Still open:** no profile-id / fetch-generation guard — stale XHR completions can still apply to a different profile at the same `idx` after rediscover/rebuild.